domain: podweb.info
author: Manuel Geissberger
[-meta]

[h1] Welcome to Podweb

[h2] What is Podweb?

[p-]
Podweb is a small, cozy corner of the internet living inside Picotron.
Every user gets their own space on podnet - a bit of cloud storage tied
to their Lexaloffle account. Podweb turns that storage into a browsable
web of pages, connected by links and explored through this browser.
[-p]

[p-]
Think of it like the early internet: simple pages, plain text, hand-crafted
by people who just want to share something. No tracking, no algorithms,
no age verification. Just Picotron users making little homes on the net
and linking to each other.
[-p]

[h2] How it works

[p-]
Each user can place an index.podweb file in their podnet folder.
This browser fetches that file and renders it. Links let you hop from
one user's page to another. Over time, friendly domain names can replace
the raw numeric user IDs - stored locally after your first visit.
[-p]

